did.abstract: Leaves of incunabula collected by Francis Fitz Randolph.

bioghist.head: Biographical Note
bioghist.p: Francis Fitz Randolph held degrees from Yale and Harvard, was an investment banker who held high-level positions at a number of corporations, and served as a trustee of Vassar College from 1947-1956. He donated a number of rare books and works of art to Vassar. He died on 12 October 1973.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: Leaves of incunabula collected by Francis Fitz Randolph.

accessrestrict.head: Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research according to the regulations of the Vassar College Archives and Special Collections Library without any additional restrictions.

userestrict.head: Restrictions on Use
